snippet.textDisplay: The visual cultural aspect is good, the intention of showcasing Kashmir is good. The immature display of "having fun while playing" sucks. When the music doesn't sound right, no overacting / forced smiles will help. Hell, in the intro, the drummer hit the cymbals and the audio is of drums (floor toms most likely). And this happened twice. It's just drama, no music. No issue with it being drama, but coming from Coke Studio India? Sucks!
snippet.textOriginal: The visual cultural aspect is good, the intention of showcasing Kashmir is good. The immature display of "having fun while playing" sucks.
